</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="851CAF2271E396FBB807108D7273ACA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="4BA0509E536899F6B71C74384670E6D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F771C344D636746226EA504BA2C4016" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="90078D1CF30B52417583717131A4A8AD" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Pleopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleopeltis macrocarpa" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrocarpa">Pleopeltis macrocarpa</taxonomicName>
(Bory ex Willd) Kaulf., species from which it was previously recognized as the variety 
<taxonomicName id="EC92374E67F750F3C2DE5EC0D64B4783" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Pleopeltis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pleopeltis macrocarpa var. laciniata" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="macrocarpa" variety="laciniata">Pleopeltis macrocarpa var. laciniata</taxonomicName>
Stolze, by the laminar scales concolorous with laciniate margins (
<bibRefCitation id="556C48BB2AA0A3A0896B484648C14975" author="Tryon, R. M." journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana, Botany New Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" pagination="1 - 190" title="Pteridophyta of Peru. Part V. 18. Aspleniaceae - 21. Polypodiaceae" volume="32" year="1993">Tryon et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
). It can also be recognized by the larger lamina and also by its shape, with broad to narrow-cuneate base (
<bibRefCitation id="B1364190D91B8A3BB3C7F28509696460" author="Tryon, R. M." journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana, Botany New Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" pagination="1 - 190" title="Pteridophyta of Peru. Part V. 18. Aspleniaceae - 21. Polypodiaceae" volume="32" year="1993">Tryon et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
